Apple will hold its 28th annual Worldwide Developers Conference (WWDC) from 5-9 June. The event will take place at the McEnery Convention Center in San Jose. The conference is focussed on innovation and apps which can be used on the iPhone, iPad, Apple Watch, Apple TV, and Mac platforms. WWDC 2017 will give developers access to more than 1,000 Apple engineers, with opportunities to meet and engage with them. The conference will also be live-streamed through the Apple Developer website (developer.apple.com/wwdc) and on the WWDC app.